<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-373-792  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 373 792.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  June 19 1989 n253 p44(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI plans big plant in Texas. (MCI Communications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Abel, Glen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp announced its plans to invest $23 millionin the construction of a 400,000-square-foot facility on a 43-acresite near Richardson, TX.andP;  The move is part of consolidation planswhich will see the communications supplier combine its networkconstruction, design and engineering groups in a single location.andO;With the 1,000 employees in the new facility, MCI will have 2,200employees in the Dallas area.andP;  The move will also put MCI within afive-mile radius of its key switching and transmission suppliers,Northern Telecom Inc's Data Communications and Network Group andDSC Communications Corp. The announcement coincided with MCI'sannouncement of its largest contract ever, a five-year, $150million agreement with Merrill Lynch andamp; Co for a worldwide networkfor voice and data communications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (planning).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Facility ConstructionPersonnelPlanningSales ContractsEquipment Acquisition.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>